1. The four pillars of the Balanced Scorecard are:
solution : D. Customer Perceptions, Financial Performance, Operational Efficiency, Organizational Knowledge and Capabilities

2. In the customer and stakeholder pillar, what common measure relies on social considerations to help gauge potential retention and repeat purchases?
solution : D. Net PRomoter Score (NPS)

3. When McDonald's adopted an all-day breakfast menu, what Drucker-style principles were they embracing?
solution : D. Listening and engaging customers to find out what they value, then adjusting operations to deliver it
